txt2img tab.label: Sampling method
txt2img tab.hint: Which algorithm to use to produce the image

txt2img tab.label: Sampling steps
txt2img tab.hint: How many times to improve the generated image iteratively; higher values take longer; very low values can produce bad results

txt2img tab.label: Restore faces
txt2img tab.hint: Use a pre-trained model to correct the generated faces. See GFPGAN or Codeformer.

txt2img tab.label: Tiling
txt2img tab.hint: Produce an image that can be tiled

txt2img tab.label: Hires fix
txt2img tab.hint: Use a similar process as image to image to upscale and add detail to the final image.

txt2img tab.label: Denoising strength
txt2img tab.hint: Determines how little respect the algorithm should have for image's content. At 0, nothing will change, and at 1 you'll get an unrelated image. With values below 1.0, processing will take less steps than the Sampling Steps slider specifies

txt2img tab.label: Hires steps
txt2img tab.hint: Number of sampling steps for upscaled picture. If 0, uses same as for original

txt2img tab.label: Upscaler
txt2img tab.hint: Which pre-tarined model to use for the upscaling process.

txt2img tab.label: Upscale by
txt2img tab.hint: Adjusts the size of the image by multiplying the original width and height by the selected value. Ignored if either Resize width to or Resize height to are non-zero

txt2img tab.label: Resize width to
txt2img tab.hint: Resizes image to this width. If 0, width is inferred from either of two nearby sliders

txt2img tab.label: Resize height to
txt2img tab.hint: Resizes image to this height. If 0, height is inferred from either of two nearby sliders

txt2img tab.label: Width
txt2img tab.hint: Image width

txt2img tab.label: Height
txt2img tab.hint: Image height

txt2img tab.label: Batch count
txt2img tab.hint: How many batches of images to create (has no impact on generation performance or VRAM usage)

txt2img tab.label: Batch size
txt2img tab.hint: How many image to create in a single batch (increases generation performance at cost of higher VRAM usage)

txt2img tab.label: CFG Scale
txt2img tab.hint: Classifier Free Guidance scale: how strongly the image should conform to prompt. Lower values produce more creative results, higher values make it follow the prompt more strictly; recommended values between 5-10

txt2img tab.label: CLIP skip
txt2img tab.hint: Clip skip is a feature that allows users to control the level of specificity of the prompt, the higher the CLIP skip value, the less deep the prompt will be interpreted. CLIP Skip 1 is typical while some anime models produce better results at  CLIP skip 2

txt2img tab.label: Seed
txt2img tab.hint: A value that determines the output of random number generator - if you create an image with same parameters and seed as another image, you'll get the same result

txt2img tab.label: Extra
txt2img tab.hint: Show additional options

txt2img tab.label: Variation seed
txt2img tab.hint: Seed of a different picture to be mixed into the generation

txt2img tab.label: Variation strength
txt2img tab.hint: How strong of a variation to produce. At 0, there will be no effect. At 1, you will get the complete picture with variation seed (except for ancestral samplers, where you will just get something)

txt2img tab.label: Resize seed from width
txt2img tab.hint: Make an attempt to produce a picture similar to what would have been produced with same seed at specified resolution

txt2img tab.label: Resize seed from height
txt2img tab.hint: Make an attempt to produce a picture similar to what would have been produced with same seed at specified resolution

txt2img tab.label: Override settings
txt2img tab.hint: If you read in generation parameters through 'Process Image tab' and individual generation parameters should deviate from your system settings, this box will be populated with those settings to override your system configuration for this workflow

process tab.hint: Process all images in a folder

process tab.label: Scale by
process tab.hint: Use this tab to resize the source image(s) by a chosen factor

process tab.label: Scale to
process tab.hint: Use this tab to resize the source image(s) to a chosen target size

process tab.label: Input directory
process tab.hint: Folder where the images are that you want to process

process tab.label: Show result images
process tab.hint: Enable to show the processed images in the image pane

process tab.label: Resize
process tab.hint: Factor for resizing 1x mean no upscale, 4x means 4 times upscale, high values might lead to memory issues on small graphics cards

process tab.label: Crop to fit
process tab.hint: If the dimensions of your source image (e.g. 512x510) deviate from your target dimensions (e.g. 1024x768) this function will fit your upscaled image into your target size image. Excess will be cropped

process tab.label: Secondary Upscaler

img2img tab.label: Resize fixed
img2img tab.hint: Resize image to target resolution. Unless height and width match, you will get incorrect aspect ratio

img2img tab.label: Crop and resize
img2img tab.hint: Resize the image so that entirety of target resolution is filled with the image. Crop parts that stick out

img2img tab.label: Resize and fill
img2img tab.hint: Resize the image so that entirety of image is inside target resolution. Fill empty space with image's colors

img2img tab.label: Mask blur
img2img tab.hint: How much to blur the mask before processing, in pixels

img2img tab.label: fill
img2img tab.hint: fill it with colors of the image

img2img tab.label: latent noise
img2img tab.hint: fill it with latent space noise

img2img tab.label: latent nothing
img2img tab.hint: fill it with latent space zeroes
